WellMind (Mental Health Support AI) - How to run

Requirements
- Python 3.x
- MySQL Server running on localhost (default port 3306)

1) Clone and open this folder

2) Create a virtual environment and install dependencies
PowerShell:
  python -m venv .venv
  .\.venv\Scripts\python.exe -m pip install --upgrade pip
  .\.venv\Scripts\python.exe -m pip install -r requirements.txt

3) Configure environment variables
- Copy `.env.example` -> `.env` and fill in values:
  - FLASK_SECRET_KEY
  - DB_HOST, DB_PORT, DB_USER, DB_PASSWORD, DB_NAME

4) Create the MySQL database + table (one-time)
Run in a MySQL client:
  CREATE DATABASE IF NOT EXISTS chatbot;
  USE chatbot;
  CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS users (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(255) UNIQUE NOT NULL,
    password VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
  );

5) Start the app
  .\.venv\Scripts\python.exe run_project.py

6) Open in browser
  http://127.0.0.1:5000

Predefined user login (if present in your DB)
- Username: admin
- Password: 123456
